def missing_val(df):
    # Total Number of missing vales
    print("Total Number of missing vales:", df.isnull().sum().sum())
    print("*"*20)
    
    # Number of missing vales
    number  = df.isnull().sum()
    print("Number of missing vales in each column")
    print(number[number >1])
    print("*"*20)

    # percent of missing vales
    percentages = round(df.isnull().sum() * 100/ len(df),3)
    print("percentage of missing vales in each column")
    print(percentages[percentages>0])
    print("*"*20)
    return

Performing INNER JOIN to JOIN all four data_tables¶

In [30]:
final_data = pd.read_sql_query("SELECT l.loan_id, l.account_number, l.customer_id, l.enterprise_id, l.screening_date,\
                                l.product_code, l.hub_id, e.business_type, e.business_activity, e.business_sector,\
                                s.ManagAgeui_APP, s.BusinFormalityOfTheBusinessui, s.ManagCBscoreui_APP,\
                                d.net_disbursement_magnitude, d.transaction_Date\
                                FROM loan_information l\
                                LEFT JOIN enteprise_information e     ON e.enterprise_id = l.enterprise_id\
                                LEFT JOIN scores_information s        ON s.loan_id = l.loan_id\
                                LEFT JOIN disbursements_information d ON d.account_number = l.account_number\
                                ", connect)
In [31]:
final_data.to_csv('final_data.csv', index=False)

def draw_multivarient_plot(dataset, rows, cols, plot_type):
    column_names=dataset.columns.values
    number_of_column=len(column_names)
    fig, axarr=plt.subplots(rows,cols, figsize=(16,10))

    counter=0
    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(cols):
             
            if counter>(number_of_column-1):
                break
            if 'violin' in plot_type:
                sns.violinplot(x='target', y=column_names[counter],data=dataset, ax=axarr[i][j])
            elif 'box'in plot_type :
                sns.boxplot(x='target', y=column_names[counter],data=dataset, ax=axarr[i][j])
            elif 'point' in plot_type:
                sns.pointplot(x='target',y=column_names[counter],data=dataset, ax=axarr[i][j])
            elif 'bar' in plot_type:
                sns.barplot(x='target',y=column_names[counter],data=dataset, ax=axarr[i][j])
                
            counter+=1

Distribution graphs (histogram/bar graph) of column data¶

In [74]:
# Distribution graphs (histogram/bar graph) of column data
def plotPerColumnDistribution(df, nGraphShown, nGraphPerRow):
    nunique = df.nunique()
    df = df[[col for col in df if nunique[col] > 1 and nunique[col] < 50]] # For displaying purposes, pick columns that have between 1 and 50 unique values
    nRow, nCol = df.shape
    columnNames = list(df)
    nGraphRow = (nCol + nGraphPerRow - 1) / nGraphPerRow
    plt.figure(num = None, figsize = (6 * nGraphPerRow, 8 * nGraphRow), dpi = 80, facecolor = 'w', edgecolor = 'k')
    for i in range(min(nCol, nGraphShown)):
        plt.subplot(nGraphRow, nGraphPerRow, i + 1)
        columnDf = df.iloc[:, i]
        if (not np.issubdtype(type(columnDf.iloc[0]), np.number)):
            valueCounts = columnDf.value_counts()
            valueCounts.plot.bar()
        else:
            columnDf.hist()
        plt.ylabel('counts')
        plt.xticks(rotation = 90)
        plt.title(f'{columnNames[i]} (column {i})')
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 1.0, w_pad = 1.0, h_pad = 1.0)
    plt.show()

Scatter and density plots¶

In [76]:
# Scatter and density plots
def plotScatterMatrix(df, plotSize, textSize):
    df = df.select_dtypes(include =[np.number]) # keep only numerical columns
    # Remove rows and columns that would lead to df being singular
    df = df.dropna('columns')
    df = df[[col for col in df if df[col].nunique() > 1]] # keep columns where there are more than 1 unique values
    columnNames = list(df)
    if len(columnNames) > 10: # reduce the number of columns for matrix inversion of kernel density plots
        columnNames = columnNames[:10]
    df = df[columnNames]
    ax = pd.plotting.scatter_matrix(df, alpha=0.75, figsize=[plotSize, plotSize], diagonal='kde')
    corrs = df.corr().values
    for i, j in zip(*plt.np.triu_indices_from(ax, k = 1)):
        ax[i, j].annotate('Corr. coef = %.3f' % corrs[i, j], (0.8, 0.2), xycoords='axes fraction', ha='center', va='center', size=textSize)
    plt.suptitle('Scatter and Density Plot')
    plt.show()

In [84]:
def predict(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train, y_train)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test, y_test)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ', cv)
    
    result_train.append(round((clf.score(X_train, y_train)*100), 3))
    result_test.append(round((clf.score(X_test, y_test)*100), 3))
    result_f1.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

In [109]:
def predict_pca(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_pca)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_pca, y_train_pca)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_pca)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_pca, y_test_pca)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_pca, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_pca, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_pca, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_pca, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_pca, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_pca, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_pca, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_pca)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_pca,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_pca, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_pca,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X_pca, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ', cv)
    
    result_train_pca.append(round((clf.score(X_train_pca, y_train_pca)*100), 3))
    result_test_pca.append(round((clf.score(X_test_pca, y_test_pca)*100), 3))
    result_f1_pca.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_pca.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_pca,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_pca.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_fi, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_fi, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_fi, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_fi, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_fi, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_fi, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_fi)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_fi,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_fi, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_fi,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X_new, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ',cv )
    
    result_train_fi.append(round((clf.score(X_train_fi, y_train_fi)*100), 3))
    result_test_fi.append(round((clf.score(X_test_fi, y_test_fi)*100), 3))
    result_f1_fi.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_fi.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_fi,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_fi.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

In [161]:
def predict_down(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_down, y_train_down)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_down, y_train_down)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_down)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_down, y_test_down)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_down, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_down, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_down, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_down, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_down, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_down, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_down, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_down)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_down,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_down, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_down,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ',cv )
    
    result_train_down.append(round((clf.score(X_train_down, y_train_down)*100), 3))
    result_test_down.append(round((clf.score(X_test_down, y_test_down)*100), 3))
    result_f1_down.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_down.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_down,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_down.append(round((cv*100), 3)) 
    return

In [178]:
def predict_sm(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_sm, y_train_sm)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_sm, y_train_sm)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_sm)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_sm, y_test_sm)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_sm, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_sm, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_sm, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_sm, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_sm, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_sm, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_sm, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_sm)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_sm,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_sm, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_sm,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X_sm, y_sm, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ',cv )
    
    result_train_sm.append(round((clf.score(X_train_sm, y_train_sm)*100), 3))
    result_test_sm.append(round((clf.score(X_test_sm, y_test_sm)*100), 3))
    result_f1_sm.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_sm.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_sm,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_sm.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return
